        "category": "analysis",
        "title": "Cartoon: Russia’s war fatigue grows",
        "title_zh": "漫画:俄罗斯的战争疲劳感日益增长",
        "url": "https://www.economist.com/node/2026-06-27/3",
        "summary_md": "### 🌟 一句话核心主旨\n2026年6月25日《经济学人》「本周世界」(The world this week)栏目发布一幅讽刺漫画,主题为「Russia's war fatigue grows」(俄罗斯的战争疲劳感日益增长),以轻松笔触折射俄方在军事、经济与政治层面的多重困境。\n\n### 🔍 核心观点与论据拆解\n1. 漫画发表于2026年6月25日,属于《经济学人》漫画(Cartoon)板块,栏目定位为「a lighter take on the news」(以轻松方式解读新闻)。\n2. 该页面为漫画导读性质,正文极简,核心仅一张漫画作品,围绕俄罗斯战争疲劳感持续加剧这一主题展开。\n3. 页面附四篇深度报道链接,作为读者延伸阅读素材,第一篇为2026年6月23日「Russia's Crimean conquest is turning into a deadly mess」(俄罗斯对克里米亚的征服正演变成致命泥潭)。\n4. 第二篇为2026年6月22日「Russia's war economy has problems—but is not about to crash」(俄罗斯战时经济存在问题,但并未濒临崩溃),指出俄经济承压但短期不会瓦解。\n5. 第三、四篇分别为2026年5月6日「Vladimir Putin is losing his grip on Russia」(弗拉基米尔·普京正在失去对俄罗斯的掌控)与2026年5月10日「Russia is stumbling on the battlefield」(俄罗斯在战场上步履蹒跚),共同暗示其政治权威与军事表现双双受挫。\n\n### 🤨 争议与潜在挑战\n原文未涉及明显争议(该页为漫画导读,未呈现双方具体论点与辩论细节)\n\n### 🔮 未来趋势预判\n基于关联报道主题推断,《经济学人》认为俄罗斯短期内将持续面临战场失利、经济承压与领导层掌控力削弱的三重困境;尽管经济不会立即崩溃,战争疲劳情绪仍可能在俄罗斯社会进一步蔓延,成为塑造其内外政策走向的重要变量。",
        "content_raw": "<p><span class=\"te_section_title\">The world this week</span></p>\n<h1>Cartoon: Russia’s war fatigue grows</h1>\n<h3>A lighter take on the news</h3>\n<h3>June 25th 2026</h3>\n<p>Dig deeper into the subjects of this week’s cartoon:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.economist.com/europe/2026/06/23/russias-crimean-conquest-is-turning-into-a-deadly-mess\">Russia’s Crimean conquest is turning into a deadly mess</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2026/06/22/russias-war-economy-has-problems-but-is-not-about-to-crash\">Russia’s war economy has problems—but is not about to crash</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.economist.com/by-invitation/2026/05/06/vladimir-putin-is-losing-his-grip-on-russia\">Vladimir Putin is losing his grip on Russia</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.economist.com/europe/2026/05/10/russia-is-stumbling-on-the-battlefield\">Russia is stumbling on the battlefield</a></p>\n<p>You can see previous ones <a href=\"https://www.economist.com/topics/cartoons\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>This article was downloaded by <a class=\"producer_link\" href=\"https://z-lib.io\">zlibrary</a> from <a class=\"origin_link\" href=\"https://www.economist.com//the-world-this-week/2026/06/25/cartoon-russias-war-fatigue-grows\">https://www.economist.com//the-world-this-week/2026/06/25/cartoon-russias-war-fatigue-grows</a> </p>",
